As I’ve navigated my journey as a filmmaker, I always wished there was a space for like-minded creatives to tap into and build together. 👐

During quarantine we were able to see what Clubhouse could do to connect people in our industry and provide a platform for networking, inspiration, and growth.

That ended.

And then I thought….

Why don’t we have that IRL??

Welcome to THE PRODUCTION CLUB - a place where creatives at all levels can build their network, gain valuable career insight, find collaborators, and learn from some of the top talent in our industry today.

When? The first Wednesday of every month at The Victorian in Santa Monica - it’s gonna be a party!! 🎉 

To kick off the first event, we’re bringing in the brilliant minds of ROB WITT (@robwittdidit) and CHRISTIAN BRESLAUER (@christhedirector) for a live discussion and Q&A. Two of the dopest trailblazers in our industry!!

Following the Q&A is a networking mixer where you can chop it up with all your fellow filmmakers and production friends. 🤌

We’ll even have some magic by world renowned magician ERIK BLACKWELL (@blackwellmagicc) 🪄 

Every month will be different speakers, panels, and guests.

Let’s build this community together!!✊✊✊

See you Wednesday, March 1!! 📆

RSVP at the link in my bio and follow @theproduction.club for all updates and event info.. SEATING IS LIMITED FOR THE Q&A 🎥🎥🎥

LFGOOOOOO!!! 🤝🏁

Time to enter a new era… @theproduction.club 🎥 🚀 

Couldn’t be more ecstatic about yesterdays launch of my new side project - THE PRODUCTION CLUB. The goal is to not only inspire and educate the next generation of filmmakers, but to create a space where we can network and build a community.

To see everyone’s faces there and get such positive feedback was truly special. The energy was CRAZY!! Over 400 people turned out!

Thank you so much to my friends @robwittdidit & @christhedirector for being my first guests!! Y’all killed it!!!

& HUGEEE thanks to all the volunteers who helped me set up, and @thevictoriansm for letting us create our very own clubhouse 🏠 

Can’t wait for the next one!!!

📸: @directedbyjoseph

Friends & Fam — we need your help!! 💰🎬

We’re raising money via @seedandspark to shoot a short film titled 𝐁𝐄𝐅𝐎𝐑𝐄 𝐈 𝐆𝐎 in New Jersey this May!! 

This is a project I’m extremely passionate about directing & executive producing — and I’ll be matching all the donations dollar for dollar to get it made!! 💵

Based on a script by @topnotch1210, the film will star @veronikadash and #KenKing 🎭 

We have an amazing team lined up that includes @b.a.cinema (DP), @producershay (Producer), @tarnovetska (SFX Makeup), @shannoncgriffin (Editor) and many more!

“𝐁𝐄𝐅𝐎𝐑𝐄 𝐈 𝐆𝐎 is a psychological drama that follows Emily, a once vibrant and beautiful woman, as she confronts her ex-boyfriend for the first time since he sold her into sex-trafficking years prior. 

As their conversation unfolds, we peel back the layers of their characters as they wrestle with their fragmented past and the emotional pain Emily has endured. This dangerous and dramatic encounter blurs the line between reality and imagination as Emily grapples with how Tristan has stripped her of her youth, her innocence and her identity. 

Will Emily get the revenge and closure that she has longed for?”

The funds will go towards hard costs to get the film made… every dollar helps!!!!

Special thanks to @kristophermanga & @iamdavidaure for helping us shoot our #seedandspark fundraiser video ✨ 

Artwork created by the legend @themovieposterguy 🔌

The link to donate is in my bio now!! Thank you!!! 🙏🙏🙏

Knowledge is power, 𝓬𝓸𝓶𝓶𝓾𝓷𝓲𝓽𝔂 is strength ✊

@anthonymandler is literally the reason why I started directing music videos. I remember sitting at USC studying his visuals and being so inspired by his cinematic approach. He married filmmaking and videos in a way I had never seen or felt before. It was infectious. I must of watched Jay-Z “Run This Town” and “Young Forever” at least 1000 times. 

When @travandres introduced me to Mandler right after I graduated in 2011, he graciously had lunch with me and gave me some game that launched me into my career. His hunger, drive, and certainty about his vision was contagious. He wasn’t a video director, he was a filmmaker. And I left so inspired. 

His body of work has shifted culture, and inspired a whole generation of directors. I’m beyond excited to have the opportunity to sit down with him at the next @theproductionclubla event to discuss his profound career and share his knowledge with everyone!! 🏠 

#May3 #TheProductionClub #AnthonyMandler

We are thrilled to announce our upcoming @productionconnect event for JULY 05, featuring two mega stars in the production community: EV SALOMON (@hatianev) & HANNAH LUX DAVIS (@hannahluxdavis) 🎥 ✨ Get ready to dive into their worlds and learn from these industry luminaries. 

🌟 Event Details:
📆 Date: Wednesday, July 5th
⏰ Time: 7pm (doors open)
📍 Location: The Victorian Santa Monica

🔥 Join us for an unforgettable evening where Ev Salomon and Hannah Lux Davis, renowned experts in their fields, will share their knowledge and experiences in the world of production. From music videos to commercials, they are behind some of the most captivating and iconic visuals today.

💡 Ev Salomon is a visionary 1st assistant director known for his exceptional work with A-list musicians, brands, and directors.

💫 Hannah Lux Davis, a distinguished music video director, has helmed iconic visuals for chart-topping artists worldwide. Her creativity and meticulous attention to detail have made her one of the most sought-after directors in the entertainment industry.

📚 At ℙ𝕣𝕠𝕕𝕦𝕔𝕥𝕚𝕠𝕟 ℂ𝕠𝕟𝕟𝕖𝕔𝕥 you'll gain insights into their creative processes, learn about the challenges they've faced, and discover how they approach each project to create breathtaking results. Whether you're an aspiring filmmaker, photographer, or simply passionate about the art of production, this event is not to be missed!

🎟 Limited spots available! RSVP now to secure your place and be part of this remarkable evening of inspiration and knowledge sharing. Link to RSVP in bio.

📸 Don't forget to spread the word! Tag your friends who would love to join us and use the hashtag #ProductionConnect to share your excitement. Let's make this event unforgettable together!

See you on July 5th! ✨🎬

In Wyoming for a shoot, and I look over to my right and there is Harrison Ford. Right next to me. By himself waiting for his ride. I introduce myself and we have a 10 minute convo about filmmaking. I asked him what is one piece of advice he could give me as an up and coming film director … he looked at me and said profoundly: “don’t quit”. Nicest guy ever. Now I have no choice but to never quit as I made a deal with a film god. 🎥🤠

We’re back this Wednesday!! I wanted to share my gratitude for the @productionconnect community that has come together to make these events possible. When we first launched, I wasn’t sure what to expect, but the support from everyone has been astounding. 

It’s a lot of fun for me to bring out friends in the industry that I admire and respect. Such is the case with our two guests this week - Ari operated Steadicam on some of my first music videos, then went off to shoot La La Land which launched him on an incredible trajectory in the film world. Recently I convinced him to operate a oner for me in my @blink182 video Darkside 😎

JD I met through Veronika when he was an assistant at JJ Abram’s Bad Robot. With the mentorship of JJ, he shot his first film on a shoe string budget - it went to Sundance and the rest is history. His most recent film Devotion is a masterpiece. 

It’s great to know that collectively we are building something bigger than ourselves for both newcomers and industry vets. I hope you all are having as much fun as I am every month!

For those interested in more info or wondering how to support, please email us (info@productionconnect.club). 

If you’d like to see the community continue to grow, please share / follow / promote us in your networks!

& as always special thanks to @thedijital & @thevictoriansm for hosting us every month 🏠

These photos don’t even scratch the surface of what I was able to accomplish this past year 🤯 through ups and downs, my main goals were to 1) lead with intention 2) let go of things that no longer served me and 3) step outside my comfort zone ✅✅✅

This new year is about doubling down and being obsessed with becoming stronger, healthier, wiser and wealthier in every way. Accepting imperfections is 🔑 as long as the eye stays on the prize. 🏆 

Although I’m sharing my highlight reel I know there are a lot of heavy things going on in the world right now. My heart goes out to everyone, everywhere. 🤍

I wouldn’t be anywhere without those who support me on this journey. You all know who you are. Thank you. Let’s level up 🚀🚀🚀 #2024 🐉

Here. We. Go. 🥵 Let’s kick off 2024 with a bang! Introducing a new format - in this 𝐏𝐑𝐎𝐃𝐔𝐂𝐓𝐈𝐎𝐍 𝐑𝐎𝐔𝐍𝐃𝐓𝐀𝐁𝐋𝐄 panel you will hear from an eclectic group of thought leaders in our industry discussing the current commercial, music video, & branded content landscape…

BYRON ATIENZA (@byron) is an award-winning Filipino-American Executive Creative Director and Filmmaker. Previously running creative at Spotify Studios and Capitol Music Group, Byron is currently working in the music & tech space and recently founded the collective A Bunch of Savages. 

JENNIFER HEATH (@radicalmedia) has worked at RadicalMedia as a Director’s Rep and Executive Producer for over 20 years. Through her career, she has had the opportunity to work with a number of acclaimed and award-winning directors, including Michael Gondry and Dave Meyers. She’s produced hundreds of videos over the years, and has focused on expanding outside traditional music videos.

ANDREW DONOHO (@andrewdonoho) is an acclaimed Director of music videos, commercials, and films with multiple VMA wins and over 7 billion views on his music videos. His work for Bella Porch “Build A B*tch” hit 250 million views in its first week of release, landing him a Variety cover story “ushering in a new Golden Age of music videos”.

JON BRANDON CRUZ (@jonbrandoncruz) is a commercial director, editor and motion graphics artist with a client roster that includes The Rock, Will Smith, Selena Gomez, Sony Pictures Studios, John Krasinski and more.

We will also feature on opening discussion from ASA PITT (@attorneyasa), Managing Partner at Pitt Entertainment Law. He’ll be giving out essential tips & guidelines for successful deal-making and contracts in the entertainment industry.

Hosted by PC Founder & Director/Producer ANDREW SANDLER (@andrew_sandler) 🎥
